# Permissions, VPC & the stack

## Two IAM sides

- **Execution role** — *what* the function can do (assumed at runtime; least privilege)
- **Resource policy** — *who* may invoke it (auto-added by triggers; manual for cross-account)

## VPC reachability

Default: **outside the VPC** — internet ✓, private ✗. Attach to a subnet → private ✓, but **internet needs a NAT**. Hyperplane ENIs → cold-start overhead negligible.

## Fronting + the serverless stack

- **Function URL** — built-in HTTPS, one per function → webhooks, prototypes
- **API Gateway** — production front (routing, throttling, keys, caching, authorizers)

Stack: **DynamoDB · S3 · SQS/SNS/EventBridge · Step Functions · Aurora Serverless · Cognito** — each scales + bills per use.
